item.title: Percussive Re-Socialization
item.description: Socialization are the processes, endorsements, and sanctions placed on us by others to direct socially acceptable behavior. These behaviors generally flow in a moral, ethical, prosocial direction. However, once we reach adulthood, we leave behind friends and family, and are left with other individuals to do our socialization. The iterative, tertiary forms of this are known as resocialization. We bump into barriers of what's not ok. Sometimes, the barriers bump us. Percussive Resocialization (pending publication) are forms of violent resocialization when other socializing agents violently failed. This is an expression of anti-fragility, wherein the socializing agents take action not just to maintain equilibrium, but to improve the environment by correcting antisocial behaviors. Normalspeak: punching nazis is good for the Earth.

item.title: An Atlas a day!
item.description: Sorry for such a long delay in sharing the boy. Life has been life, and I’m just tired. It’s also been below 0°f or just barely above for weeks. Yesterday was a hard day, and I let myself breakdown. And I was met with love and cocoa and fried zucchini and flowers and space to bawl my eyes out into the sweater of someone I love (and that wasn’t Atlas). Today is still hard, but I think I’m learning that sometimes, succumbing to a breakdown and finally finding the space to be loved so tenderly through it is its own act of healing. And maybe resistance. I’ve taken a lot of action steps today and over the past few days to take care of myself and my community and my people. I’m growing my knowledge and practice of mutual aid. It’s all we have right now. And that’s how we take the power back. And I’ve been fueled by Seeming (if you don’t know Alex Reed’s music, go find it right now) and Rage Against the Machine. I’m scared and I’m inspired and I’m filled with rage and love. I’m just a fucking human, and it’s taken me a long time to realize that. Anyway, we went on a little drive for some things and Atlas got a lot of goodies, including a duck foot. He’s been the goodest boy through all of this. I love him so damn much. Much love, from a boy who’s into feet and woman who wants to stab the witch-king in the face.
